          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 28:39",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), but not woven in any peculiar fashion.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Girdles.—Perhaps similar to the inner girdle of the high priest, but nowhere described particularly.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Girdles.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Perhaps similar to the inner girdle of the high priest, but nowhere described particularly.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bonnets.—Rather, caps. Plain, close-fitting caps, like those so commonly worn in Egypt, seem to be intended. The word used, migbâ’ah, is derived from gâbia’, “a cup” or “basin.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Bonnets.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "caps. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Plain, close-fitting caps, like those so commonly worn in Egypt, seem to be intended. The word used, ",
            "children": []
